                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>Israeli Representative Eban, on February 24, sent a letter to Secretary-General
                    Lie requesting the Security Council to give renewed consideration to his
                    country’s membership in the United Nations. The Council, on December 17, 1948,
                    had failed to recommend such membership; see Mr. Lovett’s memorandum of
                    conversation of December 21, 1948, <ref target="frus1948v05p2#pg_1676">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1948, volume V, Part 2, page
                        1676</ref>.</p>
                <p>The text of Mr. Eban’s letter is printed in United Nations, <hi rend="italic"
                        >Official Records of the Security Council, Fourth Tear, Supplement for March
                        1949</hi>, page 7.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
